es #2926 \r\n\r\nThere is a long road ahead, that issue should provide details on what to be done.\r\n\r\n1. This branch should receive periodic merges of `master` branch.  It will be merged into `master` whenever all checkboxes are marked \"done\".\r\n2. If new changes from revolution to be introduced, bring them in into rf-revolution1-3rd branch first, using `tools/injest-revolution` or better `datalad rerun -m \"Injest XXX from revolution\" _run_revolution_injest`, where `_run_revolution_injest` is a tag available in this repo pointing to initial injestion invocation (see also #3074 about `--explicit` which you might need)\r\n3. This (rf-revolution1) branch should always be ready to be merged into master, so not for adding broken new features to it.  It is recommended to bring new changes to this branch via a PR (i.e. to be merged into `rf-revolution1` branch)\r\n\r\n- [x] no direct mode support\r\n- [x] absorbed datalad-revolution as `datalad.revolution`\r\n- [x] datalad.revolution.tests pass\r\n    - [x] on appveyor\r\n    - [x] on travis: remaining issue seems to be solely reporting of paths from repos that are accessed through a symlink. At first glance everything is actually happening as it should, but the reported `path` has the true location of a file, not the linked path. Needs a careful look what should happen in each of the four situations.\r\n- [x] bring in replacement for `diff` from https://github.com/datalad/datalad-revolution/pull/58\r\n- [ ] RF -core to use -revolution pieces and decide on how \"joint\" API should look like - checkboxes in #2926", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https:/